  <description><![CDATA[<p>The resort sits at the foot of the mountains in <a data-udi="umb://document/cc3361d2d7a945d38852da5e20516d75" href="/{localLink:umb://document/cc3361d2d7a945d38852da5e20516d75}" title="Southern Sardinia">South Sardinia</a>, close to some of the most picturesque beaches on the island, where a seemingly-endless stretch of white sands lead to crystal-clear waters.</p>
<p>Those who want to stay active will appreciate the numerous activities on offer here, including sports courts and academies for football and dance, watersports and bicycles for rent. And when it’s time to relax there’s a fantastic spa with a large choice of treatments as well as several swimming pools. After a busy day, you’ll be spoilt for choice with nine restaurants offering delicious cuisine and bars including the champagne bar with views of the ocean.</p>
<p>Children are well-catered for with fun clubs for ages 3 up to 17. There’s also a nursery for babies and the resort offers amenities like prams, changing mats and baby baths for its youngest guests.</p>]]></description>
